---
description: Track migration metrics after completing a migration. Apply when a migration has just finished or the user asks about tracking migration effort.
applyIntelligently: true
---

After completing a migration, the agent must log metrics and archive transcripts. This is mandatory, not optional.

## 1. Log metrics

Run from the repo root:

```bash
python3 scripts/transcript-metrics.py <transcript-uuid> <template-name>
```

Optional flags:
- `--tokens N` — manual token count from the Cursor usage panel
- `--notes "..."` — any context about this run (e.g. "first attempt", "re-run after skill updates")
- `--dry-run` — preview without writing to CSV

This appends a row to `metrics/migration-log.csv` with proxy metrics (word count, turns, subagent usage) extracted from the agent transcript.

## 2. Archive transcripts

Copy the raw transcript JSONL file(s) into the template's migration directory:

```bash
cp ~/.cursor/projects/<project-dir>/agent-transcripts/<uuid>.jsonl templates/<name>/migrated/migration/transcripts/
```

This preserves the full conversation alongside the migration for future reference. Include subagent transcripts if any were created.

## Finding the transcript ID

The agent can find transcript IDs by listing files in the agent-transcripts directory. The most recently modified `.jsonl` file is typically the current conversation.

## What gets tracked

- Word count (main + subagents) as a proxy for token usage
- Conversation turns (user and assistant)
- Subagent count and word volume
- Total transcript size in bytes
- Optional manual token count from Cursor UI

## When to prompt

The agent should remind the user to provide a token count from the Cursor usage panel after the migration is complete. The user can also provide notes about the run.
